The paper deals with the problem of inferring properties of hidden networks based on observed cascades, which is a common topic in social network analysis (cs.SOC), data mining (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on community detection and the use of network structure to infer properties of the underlying network suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
